This paper discusses rating prediction in collaborative filtering, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves user behavior and preferences, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of missing data, which could be relevant to statistical learning (cs.SD).
